(170, 170, 'HOP FICTION', '', 'NOVEMBER 2014', 'US-STYLE PALE ALE.', '', 'Hop Fiction is an explosively tropical US-style Pale Ale. We rolled up our hop-dusted sleeves and put some advanced brewing techniques to work on this seasonal brew. Hop Fiction''s incredible aromas and flavours are down to a combination of early and late hops. Bags of soft, rounded citrus and stone fruit layer up on a dry light biscuit backbone. Hop Fiction, beer fact.', '', 'Don''t be scared by the amount of hops. Seriously this beer can handle them.', '', 20, 25, 5.2, 1010, 1048, 13, 6.5, 4.4, 79.2, 40, 0, '{"65":0}', '19', '', '["Jalape\\u00f1o and cream cheese poppers","Asparagus pesto pasta","Bacon and maple syrup cupcakes",""]'),
(17, 17, 'ZEITGEIST', '', 'SEPTEMBER 2008', 'ORGANIC BLACK LAGER.', '', 'Zeitgeist is an idiosyncratic alternative black lager. Its inspiration is found more than 200 years ago. Zeitgeist takes an age old classic, a forgotten masterpiece, and gives it relevance and an avant-garde edge.', '', 'Inspect the colour of the wort during boiling. If it is not quite dark enough, extend the boil by 10 - 15 mins and check again. The wort will darken during the boiling process.', '', 20, 25, 4.9, 1010, 1047.5, 120, 60, 4.3, 79, 32, 0, '{"65":0}', '15', '', '["Spicy cajun fried chicken","Pork dumplings with rich soy sauce","Cinnamon carrot cake with creamy cheese frosting",""]'),
(169, 169, 'ALL DAY LONG', '', 'NOVEMBER 2014', 'MALTY LOW ABV ALE.', '', 'Prototype Challenge 2014. All Day Long is a mild like no other. This complex, low-alcohol brew was the third of our 2014 Prototypes. Featuring a boatload of seven different speciality malts and some of our favourite hops, this beer is resinous at first, transitioning into something akin to bitter orange marmalade spread onto a thick bread crust. This is for everyone who said BrewDog would never brew a mild...', '', 'In any low ABV fermentation after primary fermentation has finished if the beer smells or tastes like wort, allow it to condition on the yeast for an extra 24 - 48 hours. This can round the profile off well.', '', 20, 25, 2.7, 1012, 1033, 42, 21, 4.4, 63.1, 30, 0, '{"65":30}', '22', '', '["Chunky orange marmalade on toast","Prawn toast with sweet chilli sauce","Lemon tart",""]'),
(167, 167, 'AB:17', '', 'OCTOBER 2014', 'THREE COFFEE RYE IMPERIAL PORTER.', '', 'A triple whammy of coffee from HasBean gives our 17th Abstrakt concept beer an intense and roasty, dark mocha character. We brewed with espresso in the mash, cafetiere in the boil, and whole roast beans in the whirlpool and the fermenter.', '', 'Use freshly ground coffee for the best aromatic hit.', '', 20, 25, 10.7, 1025, 1105, 300, 150, 4.3, 76.2, 100, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', 'Coffee 25g End\r\nCoffee 25g End\r\nDark Musvado\r\nSugar\r\n250g End', '["12hr smoked brisket","Chocolate pistachio cakes","Dulce de leche",""]'),
(168, 168, 'KONNICHIWA KITSUNE', '', 'OCTOBER 2014', 'HELLO MY NAME IS YUZU.', '', 'Named in a slight deviation from our Hello My Name Is series, Konnichiwa Kitsune is a Japanese- inspired, yuzu-infused Imperial IPA, brewed with Amarillo, Cascade and Citra. These punchy new world hops bring orange, grapefruit and lime to back up the yuzu aroma and flavour. Big mandarin notes, balanced against a caramel malt biscuity base.', '', 'Squeeze the fresh yuzu juice directly into the beer after primary fermentation is complete. Putting it in the hot wort may seem like better practice, but the juice will cook and some of the fresh citrus character will be lost.', '', 20, 25, 8.2, 1012, 1045, 30, 15, 4.4, 82.9, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '20', 'Yuzu juice 250g FV', '["Fresh seared tuna and rocket salad","Lemon meringue pie","Baked chicken with yuzu reduction",""]'),
(166, 166, 'INDIA PALE WEIZEN', '(W/WEIHENSTEPHAN)', 'SEPTEMBER 2014', 'BrewDog Versus Weihenstephan.', '', 'BrewDog vs. Weihenstephan India Pale Weizen kicked off a new direction for our collaborations. We took a simple concept (by our standards) and teamed up with the oldest brewery in the world to brew a mash-up beer using the signature styles of both breweries.\r\nIndia Pale Weizen has classic base\r\nhefeweizen aromas and flavours of\r\nbanana, clove and bubblegum, with\r\na distinctive haziness. Layered on\r\ntop of this is a tapestry of US citrus\r\nhop character. India Pale Weizen is a\r\nperfect symbiosis of traditional and\r\nmodern brewing.', '', 'Let the fermentation temperature creep up a couple of degrees higher than normal to create the characteristic banana and bubblegum aromas.', '', 20, 25, 6.2, 1010, 1056, 35, 17.5, 4, 85, 50, 0, '{"65":0}', '21', '', '["Korean barbecue nachos","Beef pho soup","Waffles with caramelised apple and powdered sugar",""]'),
(165, 165, 'THIS.IS.LAGER.', '', 'AUGUST 2014', '21ST CENTURY PILSNER.', 'SHARP. ROBUST. HONEST.', 'Brewed with 100% malt, ten times the hops of most industrial lagers and cold-conditioned for five weeks, this spicy, robust Pilsner is lager reborn.\r\nExpect a robust, full-bodied malt\r\ncharacter on the front of the tongue,\r\nspicy citrus notes as it goes back\r\nthrough the palate and an assertive\r\nbitter finish with a lemon and pepper\r\ncharacter to round things off.', '', 'The most important thing about making a lager? Fermentation temperature! Do everything you can to control the ambient temperature to 9 - 12°C. In the old days, they used to brew lager over winter, so the colder temperature gave a much preferable fermentation profile. Ferment too hot and you beer will taste like yeasty bread.', '', 20, 25, 4.7, 1007, 1043, 10, 6, 4.2, 83.7, 37, 0, '{"65":75}', '12', '', '["Mexican ceviche","Blue cheese crumbled over wedges","Gooey lemon bar",""]'),
(164, 164, 'RUSSIAN DOLL - PALE', '', 'AUGUST 2014', 'NESTING HOP BOMB.', '', 'The levels of hops vary throughout the range. We love hops, so all four beers are big, bitter badasses, but by tweaking the amount of each hop used later in the boil and during dry- hopping, we can balance the malty backbone with some unexpected flavours.\r\nSimcoe is used in the whirlpool for\r\nall four beers, and yet still lends\r\ndifferent characters to each.', '', 'Create balance through experimentation with the hop amounts and malt backbone.', '', 20, 25, 4, 1010, 1041, 45, 22.5, 5.2, 75.6, 35, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Roast chicken with vegetables and wild rice","Fresh pico de gallo with corn tortillas","Carrot cake","",""]'),
(162, 162, 'RUSSIAN DOLL - DOUBLE IPA', '', 'AUGUST 2014', 'NESTING HOP BOMB.', '', 'The levels of hops vary throughout the range. We love hops, so all four beers are big, bitter badasses, but by tweaking the amount of each hop used later in the boil and during dry- hopping, we can balance the malty backbone with some unexpected flavours.\r\nSimcoe is used in the whirlpool for\r\nall four beers, and yet still lends\r\ndifferent characters to each.', '', 'Create balance through experimentation with the hop amounts and malt backbone.', '', 20, 25, 8, 1013, 1074, 35, 17.5, 5.2, 82.4, 85, 0, '{"65":85}', '19', '', '["Strong cheddar fondue","Pork chops with spicy orange marmalade","Rich cr\\u00e8me br\\u00fbl\\u00e9e",""]'),
(163, 163, 'RUSSIAN DOLL - INDIA PALE ALE', '', 'AUGUST 2014', 'NESTING HOP BOMB.', '', 'The levels of hops vary throughout the range. We love hops, so all four beers are big, bitter badasses, but by tweaking the amount of each hop used later in the boil and during dry- hopping, we can balance the malty backbone with some unexpected flavours.\r\nSimcoe is used in the whirlpool for\r\nall four beers, and yet still lends\r\ndifferent characters to each.', '', 'Create balance through experimentation with the hop amounts and malt backbone.', '', 20, 25, 6, 1012, 1058, 25, 12.5, 5.2, 79.3, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Spicy chicken skewers","Fish tacos with hot sauce","Lemon pound cake with a ice sugar glaze","",""]'),
(160, 160, 'AMERICAN WHEAT', '', 'JULY 2014', 'HOPPY AMERICAN WHEAT.', '', 'A luscious blend of peach, blood orange and banana to make a suitably refreshing beverage that happily straddles the Atlantic.', '', 'Using a starter to get your yeast as vibrant and healthy as possible will make all the difference here.', '', 20, 25, 4.5, 1013, 1047, 10, 5, 5.3, 72, 17, 0, '{"64":90}', '21', '', '["Strawberry and citrus salad","Fish corn tacos with pomegranate salsa","Summer berry fruit parfait",""]'),
(161, 161, 'CAP DOG', '(W/CAP BREWERY)', 'AUGUST 2014', 'BLACK CASCARA IPA.', '', 'A collaboration by BrewDog and CAP with Cascara green unroasted cherry coffee beans.', '', 'Split the Cascara evenly between the mash and end of boil to really get the most out of it.', '', 20, 25, 9, 1014, 1083, 180, 90, 5.2, 83.1, 80, 0, '{"65":0}', '21', 'Cascara 500g', '["Chilli con carne","Pepper jack cheese burger on a brioche bun","Coffee cake",""]'),
(16, 16, 'AB:03', '', 'SEPTEMBER 2008', 'Barrel-Aged Imperial Ale.', '', 'This Abstrakt started life as a simple imperial Ale, but upon the addition of fresh Scottish raspberries and strawberries, and left to mature for 2 years in Invergordon whisky casks that had held whisky for over 40 years, this beer transcended into something new.', '', 'Add your hops with five minutes of the boil left in a nod to the great lambic producers of Belgium.', '', 20, 25, 10.5, 1013, 1093, 0, 0, 4.4, 80, 14, 0, '{"65":90}', '19', 'Strawberries 1kg FV\r\nRaspberries 1kg FV\r\nOak Chips 75g FV', '["Haggis spring rolls","Honey glazed duck breast","Cranachan",""]'),
(157, 157, 'RUSSIAN DOLL - BARLEY WINE', '', 'JUNE 2014', 'DOUBLE INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'Russian Doll was an experimental set of brews showcasing the effects of varying the amount and ratio of malts in the grist. The barley wine had rich, chewy dark fruit aromas balanced with a spike of zesty hops. Toffee, apricot jam and grapefruit pith, crammed into the head of our little Russian Doll family.', '', 'Age the beer in bottle for a few months at cellar temperature to allow the hot alcohol characteristic to diminish.', '', 20, 25, 10, 1020, 1097, 65, 32.5, 4.4, 79.4, 80, 0, '{"65":90}', '21', '', '["Stilton tart","Caramelised onion and ham foccacia","Dark fruit crumble",""]'),
(158, 158, 'SUB HOP', '', 'JUNE 2014', 'HOPPED-UP IMPERIAL PILSNER.', '', 'Brewed for the opening of our first bar in Italy, BrewDog Firenze. A mega-hoppy Imperial Pilsner, with toasty malt complexity and tropical New World hops.', '', 'Sit this beer aside for a month to allow it to mellow.', '', 20, 25, 8, 1016, 1077, 15, 7.5, 4.4, 79.2, 35, 0, '{"65":0}', '9', '', '["Seared lemon and herb salmon","Crab linguine","Almond biscotti",""]'),
(159, 159, 'U-BOAT', '(W/VICTORY BREWING)', 'JULY 2014', 'SMOKED PORTER COLLAB WITH VICTORY BREWING.', '', 'On the palate is a big dark malt sweetness, balanced by the blend of spicy Mittelfruh and citrussy Galena. Cocoa powder, rich dark chocolate, and ripe berries interplay with a toasty burnt sugar bitterness. The mouthfeel is thick and chewy with a treacly quality that doesn''t cloy, as it plays off against the hops and roast malt bitterness.', '', 'A good Porter is dependant on a long fermentation and cellaring process. Keep the temperature controlled as much as possible.', '', 20, 25, 8.4, 1015, 1080, 200, 100, 4.4, 81.3, 50, 0, '{"65":75}', '14', 'Try ageing on oak chips, infusing with rum raisins, or vanilla pods', '["Smoked bratwurst and mustard","Chargrilled steak","Grilled pineapple",""]'),
(155, 155, 'VOTE SEPP', '', 'MAY 2014', 'WITBIER WITH HIBISCUS.', '', 'Vote Sepp is a single hop wheat beer brewed to a session strength, with hibiscus flower, which gives it an impressively vibrant shade of pink. What Vote Sepp lacks in complexity, it more than makes up for in a perfect balance of tartness, bitterness and body.', '', 'Load hibiscus in the hot wort in a tea bag.', '', 20, 25, 3.6, 1009, 1036, 8, 4, 4.1, 75, 20, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', 'Hibiscus 37.5g Tank', '["Crab roll sushi with strawberries","Artichoke hearts and chicken melt","Caprese salad (mozzarella, tomato, basil, black pepper and sea salt)"]'),
(154, 154, 'HELLO MY NAME IS PÄIVI', '', 'MAY 2014', 'SEA BUCKTHORN DOUBLE IPA.', '', 'Brewed with sea buckthorn, a tart and bitter berry found on the Finnish coastline. Bright, vibrant aromas of tangerine, mandarin and peach, with zesty hits of lime, envelop the nutty, caramel malt backbone. The intense fruitiness gives a jammy quality to the nose. On the palate is a warm biscuity sweetness, with tropical fruits in a supporting role to a huge grapefruit and orange bitterness.', '', 'Sea buckthorn characteristics can vary from its country or origin. Taste the berries before addition to determine the best usage.', '', 20, 25, 8.3, 1013, 1076, 30, 15, 4.4, 82.9, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', 'Sea Buckthorn\r\nPuree\r\n375g End\r\nEXP 366 37.5g Dryhop', '["Korvapuusti (cinnamon and cardamom buns)","Spicy orange chicken marmalade served with potato bread","Sea buckthorn cheesecake",""]'),
(153, 153, 'DOG C', '', 'MAY 2014', 'CACAO, COFFEE CHILI ANNIVERSARY STOUT.', '', 'Our anniversary stout was based on AB:04, one of our most sought after beers ever. This beer is slightly different each year, with subtle variations coming into play purely down to environmental and fermentation factors. What doesn''t change is the rich dark chocolate, bitter coffee and chilli warmth of this monumental stout.', '', 'Be really careful when mashing, as this amount of malts can get tough to sparge! Add honey into the boil, and naga chilli and vanilla in maturation (soak them in some neutral spirit to sanitise).', '', 20, 25, 15, 1003, 1120, 100, 50, 4.4, 98, 90, 0, '{"65":0}', '19', 'Based on AB:04, but with added\r\nvanilla and 3.5 times the chilli.', '["Blackened cajun beef","Blue cheese","Flourless chocolate cheesecake"]'),
(152, 152, '#MASHTAG 2014', '', 'MAY 2014', 'DEMOCRATIC IMPERIAL RED ALE.', '', 'A slightly psychotic, orange-that- thinks-it''s-a-grapefruit character builds upon and intensifies the hop bitterness, squaring up against the rich sweet malt base. The result is a huge Red Ale with a drinkable quality you''d expect in a beer half this strength.', '', 'Experiment with different citrus juices to get a wide array of flavours and aromas in the beer.', '', 20, 25, 9, 1015, 1084, 20, 10, 4.4, 82.1, 50, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', 'Blood Orange 250g End\r\nLemon Peel 3.9g End\r\nOrange Peel 7.7g End', '["Beetroot and blood orange salad","Coriander and mango grilled steak tacos","Orange sherbet ice cream",""]'),
(151, 151, 'JASMINE IPA', '', 'MARCH 2014', 'FLORAL & FRUITY INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'This has big floral aromas backed up with some of our favourite fruity hop flavours. Bitter, bright and refreshing, our Jasmine IPA is a perfect spring beer for drinking outside (under a patio heater, with a pair of gloves on).', '', 'When dry hopping with the jasmine, use a muslin or cloth like a tea bag, and make sure it has a heavy object in it (ensure its clean).  This will help to keep the jasmine submerged in the beer for better flavour extraction.', '', 20, 25, 5.8, 1014, 1060, 35, 17.5, 4.4, 76.7, 40, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', 'Jasmine addition in cold conditioning', '["Chicken satay","Thai fishcakes","Honey and almond sponge cake",""]'),
(150, 150, 'ALPHA POP', '', 'MARCH 2014', 'HOPPY RYE PALE ALE.', '', 'A hoppy Rye Ale loaded with an avalanche of citrus and resinous flavours. Columbus, our high-alpha friend, lends a huge pithy citrus blast, with Ahtanum providing a punchy tropical fruit back-up. Brewing with rye adds a spiciness to the speciality malt caramel backbone, giving a warm ginger snap flavour, before slowly the hops, barley and rye combine and build to an orangey, biscuity, almost chocolatey crescendo.', '', 'Columbus and Ahtanum hop additions create a perfect blend of resin and lemon character.', '', 20, 25, 4.5, 1011, 1045, 25, 12.5, 4.4, 75.6, 30, 0, '{"65":0}', '19', '', '["Spicy lamb tikka masala","Spicy beef and Mexican black bean burger","Poached cinnamon apple muffins",""]'),
(149, 149, 'HELLO MY NAME IS ZÉ', '(W/2CABEÇAS)', 'MARCH 2014', 'PASSIONFRUIT IPA - 2CABECAS COLLAB.', '', 'Punk multiplied by Jack Hammer, divided by passionfruit with some Brazilian spirit factored in too. A well-rounded IPA, with bags of tropical flavour boosted by the addition of passionfruit, which unsurprisingly dominates the aroma of this summery IPA.', '', 'Try adding some of the passionfruit in the cold conditioning phase.', '', 20, 25, 6.4, 1012, 1061, 20, 10, 4.4, 80.3, 50, 0, '{"65":0}', '19', 'Passionfruit 438g End', '["Grilled lamb chops with a fruit reduction","Ginger and chilli beef stir fry","Passionfruit souffl\\u00e9",""]'),
(148, 148, 'KOHATU', 'IPA is Dead', 'FEBUARY 2014', 'SINGLE HOP INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'As you''d expect from a New Zealand hop variety, Kohatu contributes bags of tropical fruit, but with loads of lime notes, & pineapple hits. Seriously fruity, with sweet, juicy melon and stonefruit notes.', '', 'New Zealand hops are in short supply - club together with other brewers to try and get hold of some, or ask your local brewery if you can buy small amounts from them.', '', 20, 25, 7.2, 1012, 1067, 30, 15, 4.4, 82.1, 70, 0, '{"65":0}', '19', '', '["Tuna sushi roll with spicy mayonnaise sauce","Thai green curry","Pineapple upside down cake",""]'),
(146, 146, 'COMET', 'IPA is Dead', 'FEBUARY 2014', 'SINGLE HOP INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'A potently bitter hop variety originally grown in the US around 40 years ago, Comet has been newly resurrected - this German version has bold resinous grapefruit flavours, which add a huge fresh hop aroma to this IPA.', '', 'Experiment with other high alpha hops during dry-hop to discover their aroma and flavour characteristics.', '', 20, 25, 7.2, 1012, 1067, 30, 15, 4.4, 82.1, 70, 0, '{"65":0}', '19', '', '["Margherita pizza with chili flakes","Spicy Thai peanut satay","Panna cotta with a grapefruit tuile",""]'),
(147, 147, 'HBC 366', 'IPA is Dead', 'FEBUARY 2014', 'SINGLE HOP INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'A new, at-the-time un-named American hop now known as Equinox. Piney, resinous with spicy fruit notes and biting grapefruit. Stewed orange and pineapple with a resinous edge.', '', 'With new hop varieties, growers are discovering flavour attributes completely unexpected from hops, which can add unique character to your brews.', '', 20, 25, 7.2, 1012, 1067, 30, 15, 4.4, 82.1, 70, 0, '{"65":0}', '19', '', '["Spicy black bean and chicken tortilla soup","Spicy lamb tikka masala","Fruity bread pudding",""]'),
(143, 143, 'HELLO MY NAME IS VLADIMIR', '', 'JANUARY 2014', 'LIMONNIK INFUSED IMPERIAL IPA (NOT FOR GAYS).', '', 'A Limonnik-infused, triple dry- hopped double IPA. Dry berry tartness and intense citrus hop character meld with a dry bready malt base, boosted by a hint of alcohol warmth. This beer was brewed as a protest against the anti-LGBT legislation in Russia surrounding the Sochi Olympics.', '', 'If you can''t get hold of Limonnik berries, rose hips make an accessible alternative!', '', 20, 25, 8.2, 1013, 1076, 16, 8, 4.4, 83, 70, 0, '{"65":0}', '21', 'Fruit in the boil, berries in the\r\nfermenter\r\nLimonnik berries 2.5g Twist', '["Russian mini pork pies ","Beef Stroganoff","Chocolate and fruit cake",""]'),
(144, 144, 'BOURBON BABY', '', 'JANUARY 2014', 'BARREL-AGED SCOTCH ALE.', '', 'Santa Paws Scotch ale aged in bourbon barrels - light, dry and toasty, with vanilla, hints of chocolate and ginger biscuit, and a faint spicy hoppiness.', '', 'Use bourbon-soaked oak chips in secondary to achieve barrel character.', '', 20, 25, 5.8, 1005, 1049, 44, 22, 4.4, 90, 35, 0, '{"65":90}', '19', '', '["Blackened cajun beef","Pulled pork Millionaire''s shortbread",""]'),
(145, 145, 'AB:16', '', 'FEBUARY 2014', 'COFFEE-INFUSED BELGIAN QUAD.', '', 'On the nose, clove and nutmeg, cafe au lait, subtle dark fruit notes, and hints of candied lemon peel. On the palate, smooth & fruity espresso, milk chocolate, and warm brandy- soaked currants are in the middle of a high-class dance-off against the spicy and peppery Belgian character. The overall impression evokes malt loaf or ginger cake.', '', 'For the traditional cellering, age this beer in vessel or bottle for 2 - 3 months at cellar temperature.', '', 20, 25, 10.6, 1012, 1090, 30, 15, 4.4, 86.7, 55, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', 'Coffee Beans 250g FV\r\nRaisins 90g End\r\nDark sugar 140g End', '["Roasted duck","Gorgonzola and rye nut bread with smoked honey ham","Raspberry coffee cheesecake",""]'),
(142, 142, 'CLOWN KING', '', 'DECEMBER 2013', 'US STYLE BARLEY WINE.', '', 'A heavy hitting combination of rich malt flavours and relentless, bitter hops. Aromas of caramel and toasted marshmallow, with raisin and dried fruit, alongside a spicy undercurrent of resin. With toasty malt and sweet dark fruit flavours, and a smooth, chewy mouthfeel, you''ll be lulled into a false sense of security, before the intense pine-sap resin draws out a huge bitter finish.', '', 'Leave this beer to chill in the cellar for a few months to round off the flavour profile.', '', 20, 25, 12, 1020, 1130, 24, 12, 4.4, 102.3, 85, 0, '{"65":90}', '21', '', '["Aged Stilton","Flaky pastry beef pie and sweet potato mash","Chocolate pecan praline cake",""]'),
(141, 141, 'LUMBERJACK STOUT', '', 'DECEMBER 2013', 'BLUEBERRY BACON STOUT.', '', 'Lumberjack Stout is an intense beast that took its inspriation from what an actual bona-fide lumberjack might have for breakfast. Flavours of molasses, chocolate, smoke, berry, coffee and more, with a low bitterness, leaning this beer firmly towards the malty side.', '', 'Adding extra smoked malt will amp up the bacon character.', '', 20, 25, 15.2, 1020, 1110, 158, 79, 4.4, 82, 20, 0, '{"65":105}', '21', 'Blueberries, maple syrup and coffee,\r\nthen aged in ex Grain whisky casks\r\nMaple Syrup 50g End\r\nBlueberries 100g Middle', '["Maple syrup drizzled chocolate chip pancakes","Fried bacon with crispy honeycomb bits","Coffee cake",""]'),
(14, 14, 'TRASHY BLONDE', '', 'APRIL 2008', 'YOU KNOW YOU SHOULDN''T.', '', 'A titillating, neurotic, peroxide punk of a Pale Ale. Combining attitude, style, substance, and a little bit of low self esteem for good measure; what would your mother say?', '', 'Be careful not to collect too much wort from the mash. Once the sugars are all washed out there are some very unpleasant grainy tasting compounds that can be extracted into the wort.', '', 20, 25, 4.1, 1010, 1041.7, 15, 7.5, 4.4, 76, 41.5, 0, '{"69":0}', '18', '', '["Fresh crab with lemon","Garlic butter dipping sauce","Goats cheese salad","Creamy lemon bar doused in powdered sugar",""]'),
(140, 140, 'BLACK EYE JOE', '(W/STONE BREWING CO)', 'NOVEMBER 2013', 'COFFEE BLACK IPA.', '', 'A fresh tropical hit from this Black IPA, with undertones of roasted coffee. A well balanced, drinkable yet complex beer.', '', 'Be careful to select the right coffee for this brew.  For a fresh but fruity coffee hit, try to find lightly roasted Arabica beans.', '', 20, 25, 5.8, 1008, 1053, 177.3, 88.7, 4.4, 84.9, 40, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', 'Fresh coffee in the boil', '["Spicy carne asada with black beans and Mexican Rice","Pork smothered in mole sauce","Chocolate covered espresso beans",""]'),
(139, 139, 'MOSHI MOSHI 15', '', 'NOVEMBER 2013', 'AMERICAN PALE ALE BIRTHDAY BEER.', '', 'A riot of C-hops, with layers of grapefruit, lime zest, pine needles, freshly cut grass, pungent resin, layered up on toasty malt with a touch of caramel sweetness.', '', 'Some Munich malt in this beer will lift the biscuity backbone, and provide much needed balance to the heavy hitting US hops.', '', 20, 25, 5.2, 1011, 1048, 35, 17.5, 4.4, 77.1, 45, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Spicy Vietnamese vermicelli salad","Spicy fish tacos with mango chilli","Banana bread",""]'),
(138, 138, 'INTERSTELLAR', '', 'NOVEMBER 2013', '2013 PROTOTYPE RED RYE IPA.', '', 'Interstellar is a Red Rye IPA with spicy rye flavours from the malt and with great all-round spicy, fruity and earthy hop aromas from the use of Willamette and Amarillo.', '', 'Be careful with the rye malt in the run off. It can lead to stuck mashes and extended collection periods.', '', 20, 25, 6.5, 1011, 1059, 50, 25, 4.4, 81.4, 55, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Oak chip smoked salmon","Sticky spicy barbecue ribs","Scottish tablet",""]'),
(137, 137, 'HOBO POP', '', 'NOVEMBER 2013', '2013 PROTOTYPE RYE PALE ALE.', '', 'Brewed with mountains of Wheat, Rye, Cara and Crystal malts, fermented with an American ale yeast and bittered with Amarillo & Centennial, this 4.2% beer is what happens if something classy like a European wheat beer goes to live in Vegas. Zingy citrus hops and a punchy bitterness bolster this low ABV pale.', '', 'Add the rye and wheat malt evenly through the mash.', '', 20, 25, 4.2, 1010, 1042, 30, 15, 4.4, 76.2, 50, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Mozzarella and tomato baked chicken","Spiced shrimp salad","Strawberry cheescake",""]'),
(136, 136, 'BRIXTON PORTER', '', 'NOVEMBER 2013', 'PARADIGM-CHANGING PORTER.', '', 'Brixton Porter delivers bold chocolate and coffee flavours with light smokiness and hints of autumn fruit all but built on a low ABV, lighter bodied backbone. Complex and intriguing, with spicy bitterness, but very sessionable.', '', 'After the primary fermentation has finished, leave the beer in contact with the yeast for around 48 hours. Any longer and there is a risk that it will start to impart yeasty, bready flavours to the beer.', '', 20, 25, 5, 1014, 1053, 200, 100, 4.4, 73.6, 50, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Grilled rib-eye steak","Baked curry chickpea snacks","Chocolate and walnut brownie"]'),
(135, 135, 'VIC SECRET', 'IPA is Dead', 'OCTOBER 2013', 'SINGLE HOP INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'Piney, citrusy and resinous with herbal notes, Vic Secret is dual- purpose (flavour & bitterness) perfect for brewing up a single hop IPA.', '', 'You can always add more hops, but it is difficult to take them away. Carry out multiple additions of the hops during dry hopping to achieve the best profile.', '', 20, 25, 7.4, 1012, 1069, 30, 15, 4.4, 82.6, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Roasted duck","Raspberry coffee cheesecake","Gorgonzola and rye nut bread with smoked honey ham",""]'),
(132, 132, 'BAVARIAN WEIZEN', '', 'SEPTEMBER 2013', 'UNLEASH THE YEAST SERIES.', '', 'Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast.\r\nBavarian Weizen yeast adds\r\ntraditional weissbier notes of banana\r\nand clove.', '', 'Play around with the fermentation temperature to get the best flavour profile from the individual yeasts.', '', 20, 25, 6.3, 1012, 1060, 30, 15, 4.4, 80, 55, 0, '{"65":0}', '22', '', '["Spicy paella","German bratwurst with spicy mustard dip and vinaigrette salad","Creamy eggs benedict",""]'),
(133, 133, 'BELGIAN TRAPPIST', '', 'SEPTEMBER 2013', 'UNLEASH THE YEAST SERIES.', '', 'Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast.\r\nAbbey style yeasts add distinctive\r\nspicy and fruity notes, and dry out\r\nthe finished beer.', '', 'Play around with the fermentation temperature to get the best flavour profile from the individual yeasts.', '', 20, 25, 6.3, 1012, 1060, 30, 15, 4.4, 80, 55, 0, '{"65":0}', '25', '', '["Roast beef with spicy jus","Ginger bread cookies","Orange tart",""]'),
(134, 134, 'PILSEN LAGER', '', 'SEPTEMBER 2013', 'UNLEASH THE YEAST SERIES.', '', 'Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast.\r\nPilsner yeast ferments with no fruity\r\nesters or spicy phenols, although it\r\ncan add a hint of butterscotch.', '', 'Play around with the fermentation temperature to get the best flavour profile from the individual yeasts.', '', 20, 25, 6.3, 1012, 1060, 30, 15, 4.4, 80, 55, 0, '{"65":0}', '9', '', '["Spicy crab cakes","Spicy cucumber and carrot Thai salad","Sweet filled dumplings",""]'),
(131, 131, 'AMERICAN ALE', '', 'SEPTEMBER 2013', 'UNLEASH THE YEAST SERIES.', '', 'Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast.\r\nAmerican Ale used a clean\r\nfermenting strain which provides\r\nsome faint fruity notes.', '', 'Play around with the fermentation temperature to get the best flavour profile from the individual yeasts.', '', 20, 25, 6.3, 1012, 1060, 30, 15, 4.4, 80, 55, 0, '{"65":0}', '19', '', '["Fried brie bites","American cheese burger","Poached apple tart","",""]'),
(130, 130, 'BABY DOGMA', '', 'SEPTEMBER 2013', 'SESSION SCOTCH ALE.', '', 'A baby Scotch ale with dry and toasty malt flavours and hints of smoke. Toffee, biscuit and fudge abound with a spicy bitterness from the pan-global hops.', '', 'The addition of Weyermann Beech Smoked malt creates a beer with a delicate smoke character.', '', 20, 25, 4.5, 1013, 1048, 40, 20, 4.4, 72.9, 35, 0, '{"66":75}', '19', '', '["French onion soup","Braised pheasant","Caramel sauce and hot fudge",""]'),
(129, 129, 'DEAD METAPHOR', '', 'SEPTEMBER 2013', 'SCOTTISH BREAKFAST STOUT.', '', 'Scottish chocolate breakfast Stout - brewed with Brazilian SertÃ£o coffee, Venezuelan cacao and (for the Scottish element) oatmeal. Smooth, chocolately and rich, with a honeycomb mouthfeel and a rich red berry coffee character. Brewed with our beer blogger friends from The Beer Cast and Hopzine.', '', 'Steep the cocoa nibs and chocolate in the hot wort for a short period for the best extraction of flavour compounds.', '', 20, 25, 6.8, 1016, 1068, 86, 43, 4.4, 76.5, 30, 0, '{"64":75}', '19', 'Cacao 37.5g End\r\nLactose 125g End\r\nGround coffee 6.3g End', '["Brisket burnt ends","Candied bacon French toast","Coco Pops (add stout to cereal)",""]'),
(13, 13, 'CULT LAGER', '', 'APRIL 2008', 'US & NEW ZEALAND HOPPED LAGER.', '', 'A lager that actually tastes of something? You have to be kidding, right? Cult lager is made with 100% malt and whole leaf hops. Maybe we are crazy, so what? Taste our lager and we are pretty sure that you will agree that the fine line between insanity and genius has just become a little more blurred.', '', 'When the fermentation is nearly complete, allow the temperature of the beer to rise. This will scrub some of the undesirable flavours out.', '', 20, 25, 5.4, 1049, 1008, 19, 8, 4.1, 83.7, 50, 0, '{"65":75}', '10', '', '["Arrabiata pasta with grilled prawns","Mexican spiced chicken with hot sauce","Orange marmalade thumb print cookie",""]'),
(126, 126, 'DOGMA', '', 'JULY 2013', 'REVAMPED WEE HEAVY.', 'LUSCIOUS. MALTY. FRUITY.', 'Brewed with over ten different types of malt, and blended together with Scottish heather honey, it is a pantheon to the gods of intricacy and nuance; a beer that celebrates a confluence of ideas. Complex, indulgent and encapsulating, Dogma gives more than a cursory nod to history, to make you ponder the very nature of beer itself.', '', 'There''s a lot of specialty malt in the mash. Make sure you take the run off nice and steady - increase the flow too much and pull in the bed at your peril.', '', 20, 25, 7.5, 1023, 1080, 46, 23, 4.5, 70, 30, 0, '{"65":75}', '12', 'Heather Honey 125g', '["Mature cheddar with red onion chutney","Honey glazed ham","Chocolate caramel drizzled sponge cake","",""]'),
(125, 125, 'BLITZ BERLINER WEISSE', '', 'JULY 2013', 'BERLINER FRUIT BEER.', '', 'Our sour recipe for all fruit Blitz beers uses a process called kettle souring.  In this we steep a bag of malt in the wort to allow the bacteria to grow in it.', '', 'Making sour beers is an art, and is mostly related to trial and error with your process. Experiment with different temperatures for steeping the grain. 40 - 50°C will allow the lacto to grow and produce a clean profile.', '', 20, 25, 3, 1040, 1007, 9, 4.5, 3.2, 82.5, 8, 0, '{"65":60}', '19', 'Before main fermentation steep a bag of malt in the wort for 48 hours. Re boil the wort before pitching in the yeast for the main fermentation', '["Lobster bisque","Grilled salmon with a light lemon sauce","Cheesecake with raspberry (or peach\\/passion fruit) sauce",""]'),
(124, 124, 'BLACK JACQUES', '', 'JUNE 2013', 'RED WINE BARREL-AGED IMPERIAL BLACK SAISON.', '', 'A Black Saison, brewed with oats and wheat for a silky mouthfeel, Spicy hops and Carafa Malt for colour, then aged in red wine barrels. On the nose there''s cola, chocolate, coffee, mint humbug, warming oak, and spice. The myriad flavours touch on treacle, ripe banana, espresso, brandy, and a clean herbal warmth.', '', 'Addition of the grains of paradise help to accentuate the peppery spiciness of the yeast.', '', 20, 25, 11.1, 1005, 1089, 15, 7.5, 4.4, 94.4, 45, 0, '{"65":90}', '23', 'Grains of paradise 10g End (WP)\r\nLemon Peel 25g End (WP)\r\nGinger 7.5g End (WP)', '["Cured Spanish ham","Steak pasty","Black cherry tart",""]'),
(123, 123, 'EVERYDAY ANARCHY', '', 'JUNE 2013', 'WHITE WINE BARREL-AGED IMPERIAL RED SAISON.', '', 'This French white wine barrel aged Imperial Saison has a plethora of intertwining flavours. Huge aromas of peach, syrup, tangerine, sherry, toffee and raisin, followed by a dynamic bracing acidity.', '', 'The honey addition will help to dry out the beer, as the saison yeast will continue to ferment long after most ale yeast.', '', 20, 25, 10.5, 1005, 1081, 15, 7.5, 4.4, 93.8, 45, 0, '{"65":75}', '23', 'Coriander seeds 12.5g End (WP)\r\nOrange 25g End (WP)\r\nLemon 25g End (WP)\r\nHoney 125g End (WP)\r\nPink peppercorns 3.5g End (WP)', '["Spiced carrot and coriander soup","Spicy chilli king prawns","Orange zest tart",""]'),
(121, 121, 'DOG WIRED', '(W/8 WIRED)', 'JUNE 2013', 'NEW ZEALAND IMPERIAL PILSNER.', '', 'Brewed in collaboration with Soren from New Zealand''s stellar 8-Wired brewery, this is an Imperial Pilsner featuring two of our favourite New Zealand hops: Nelson Sauvin and Motueka. Sitting at a dangerously drinkable 7.1% ABV there''s a touch of Munich malt which gives this beer that little extra caramel biscuit bite to compliment the lip smackingly tropical hops. Expect an all out NZ hoppy riot.', '', 'Hold the mash for longer at 63-64°C to get more fermentability from the wort.', '', 20, 25, 7.1, 1010, 1065, 13, 6.5, 4.4, 85, 65, 0, '{"64":0}', '9', '', '["Spiced and blackened cajun chicken","Pork belly vindaloo","Rhubarb pie",""]'),
(120, 120, 'ELECTRIC INDIA', '', 'MAY 2013', 'Vibrant Hoppy Saison.', '', 'Re-brewed as a spring seasonal, this beer - which appeared originally as an Equity Punk shareholder creation - retains its trademark spicy, fruity edge. A perfect blend of Belgian Saison and US IPA, crushed peppercorns and heather honey are also added to produce a genuinely unique beer.', '', 'Source some really good heather honey to get the right spicy esters in the beer.', '', 20, 25, 5.2, 1005, 1045, 15, 7.5, 4.4, 88.9, 38, 0, '{"65":75}', '22', 'Honey 62.5g\r\nEnd\r\n(WP)\r\nCoriander Seeds 8.5g 45mins', '["Mussels with a garlic and herb sauce","Crab melt sandwich","Shortbread cookies",""]'),
(12, 12, 'STORM', '', 'DECEMBER 2007', 'ISLAY WHISKY AGED IPA.', '', 'Dark and powerful Islay magic infuses this tropical sensation of an IPA. Using the original Punk IPA as a base, we boosted the ABV to 8% giving it some extra backbone to stand up to the peated smoke imported directly from Islay.', '', 'After primary fermentation is complete, rack off into a secondary fermeter and add the oak chips to replicate the authentic Islay barrel experience.', '', 20, 25, 8, 1010, 1082, 12, 6, 4.4, 86, 60, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', 'Oak chips soaked in Islay whisky 50g ', '["Oysters","Hickory smoked ham","Rocky Road",""]'),
(118, 118, '#MASHTAG 2013', '', 'MAY 2013', 'DEMOCRATIC AMERICAN BROWN ALE.', '', 'A rich, nutty Brown Ale with a deep, rich malt profile, hopped with a range of citrusy and spicy US varieties. Mellow yet endlessly complex, with enough chocolate and fruit character to balance the bitterness, and a soft oaky roundness.', '', 'Add the hazelnuts and oak chips during the cold conditioning phase.', '', 20, 25, 7.5, 1013, 1070, 40, 20, 4.4, 81.4, 50, 0, '{"65":90}', '21', 'Roasted Hazelnuts 25g in Tank (FV)\r\nAlmonds 12.5g in Tank (FV)\r\nOak Chips 25g in Tank (FV)', '["Roast beef","Roasted butternut squash","Hazelnut brittle",""]'),
(119, 119, 'DOG B', '', 'MAY 2013', 'CACAO, COFFEE CHILI ANNIVERSARY STOUT.', '', 'Our anniversary stout was based on AB:04, one of our most sought after beers ever. This beer is slightly different each year, with subtle variations coming into play purely down to environmental and fermentation factors. What doesn''t change is the rich dark chocolate, bitter coffee and chilli warmth of this monumental Stout.', '', 'Be really careful when mashing, as this amount of malts can get tough to sparge! Add honey into the boil, and naga chili and vanilla in maturation (soak them in some neutral spirit to sanitise).', '', 20, 25, 15, 1003, 1120, 100, 50, 4.4, 98, 90, 0, '{"65":90}', '19', 'Based on AB:04, but with added\r\nvanilla and 3.5 times the chilli.\r\n\r\nFuggles 25 15 Bitter\r\nCoffee 12.5 15 Twist\r\nFuggles 25 0 Aroma\r\nCoffee 12.5 0 Twist', '["Blackened cajun beef","Blue cheese","Flourless chocolate cheesecake",""]'),
(117, 117, 'MISSPENT YOUTH', '', 'APRIL 2013', 'MILK & HONEY SCOTCH ALE.', '', 'The brainchild of our small batch brewer, George Woods. A dangerously drinkable milk sugar- infused Scotch Ale', '', 'Lots of malt in this one. Mash-in in stages, and spread the pale ale malt throughout the mash to provide stability.  If the mash starts to sink, stop, wait a few minutes while mixing, then start again.', '', 20, 25, 7.3, 1020, 1079, 120, 60, 4.4, 74.7, 30, 0, '{"67":75}', '19', 'See honey and lactose additions', '["Roasted garlic and chilli infused camembert cheese","Korean style chicken wings","Chocolate milk shake",""]'),
(116, 116, 'VICE BIER', '', 'APRIL 2013', 'Hoppy Wheat Bier.', '', 'Our take on the classic German Kristallweizen. A clear German wheat beer, layers of bubblegum and vanilla perfectly balanced with the American and New Zealand hops.', '', 'Ferment at higher or lower temperatures to select the esters that will create clove- like or banana-like flavours.', '', 20, 25, 4.3, 1010, 1043, 30, 15, 4, 81.8, 25, 0, '{"65":75}', '22', '', '["Citrus salad with balsamic dressing","Lobster","Ginger and orange cookies",""]'),
(115, 115, '10 HEADS HIGH', '', 'APRIL 2013', 'IMPERIAL RED ALE.', '', '10 Heads High is loosely based on our awesome 2011 Prototype beer Hops Kill Nazis. This is an uncompromising 7.8% Imperial Red Ale loaded high with American Hops. Think of this as an Imperial India Red Ale, or a super-charged version of 5am Saint. Either way this is a seriously good beer!', '', 'Achieve the red colour by using the ratio of Caramalt, Crystal and Dark Crystal malts.  The trick is to get the colour, without too much dried fruit character.', '', 20, 25, 7.8, 1015, 1074, 90, 45, 4.4, 79.7, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '18', '', '["Arrabiata pasta","Mulled cheddar","Toasted almond cake",""]'),
(114, 114, 'FAKE LAGER', '', 'MARCH 2013', 'BOHEMIAN PILSNER.', '', 'Fake is the new black. Fake is where it is at. Fake Art, fake brands, fake breasts, and fake lager. We want to play our part in the ugly fallout from the Lager Dream. Say hello to Fake Lager - a zesty, floral 21st century faux masterpiece with added BrewDog bitterness.', '', 'Once the primary fermentation is complete get this beer as cold as you can and let it mature for as long as you''ve got.', '', 20, 25, 4.7, 1010, 1046, 12, 6, 4.4, 78, 40, 0, '{"65":75}', '10', '', '["Fried crab cakes with avocado salsa","Spicy shredded pork roll with hot dipping sauce","Key lime pie",""]'),
(113, 113, 'BRACKEN''S PORTER', '', 'MARCH 2013', 'A TRIBUTE TO OUR FAVOURITE 4 PAWED FRIEND.', '', 'The beer was named Bracken''s Porter as a tribute to our favourite four pawed friend who sadly passed in 2013. Chocolately, robust, warming, laid back and lots of fun - there are plenty of similarities between the two. Bracken we miss you and we hope you like your beer. Long live the original BrewDog.', '', 'Try to replicate London''s highly carbonated water to really emphasise the dark malt profile.', '', 20, 25, 5, 1010, 1049, 110, 55, 4.4, 79, 50, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Grilled vegetable and chicken teriyaki skewers","Chilli covered burger (Sloppy Joe)","Candied bacon topped chocolate cheesecake",""]'),
(111, 111, 'VAGABOND PILSNER', '', 'FEBRUARY 2013', 'Hoppy Pilsner.', '', 'Take the thirst-quenching crispness of a German Pilsner and combine it with lemon and honey to produce a rewarding modern twist on a beer classic.', '', 'The addition of the acidulated malt tweaks the pH down to aid the yeast fermentation, and helps to creates the crisp lager bite.  Be careful not to use more than 10% in any grist, it will turn your mash into jelly!', '', 20, 25, 4.5, 1012, 1046, 25, 12.5, 4.4, 73.9, 55, 0, '{"65":75}', '9', '', '["Jamaican jerk chicken","Hot dog with grilled onions and spicy ketchup","Shortbread and raspberry jam thumbprint cookie",""]'),
(112, 112, 'AB:15', '', 'MARCH 2013', 'SALTED CARAMEL POPCORN STRONG ALE.', '', 'A salted caramel popcorn Imperial Ale. Bourbon and Rum barrel aged, this 12.8% ale has complex and twisting flavours. Bitter caramel, wood, smoke, spice, treacle and vanilla are all present and intertwine against a smooth and lightly chewy mouthfeel. The salted caramel popcorn lends subtle hints of a smoky brininess.', '', 'By soaking some oak chips in bourbon, then steeping in the beer you not only get an authentic Bourbon taste - the beer will also gain ABV!  Add salt to taste, too much will totally ruin the balance of the beer.', '', 20, 25, 12.8, 1020, 1096, 111, 55.5, 4.4, 79.17, 50, 0, '{"68":75}', '21', 'Adding popped popcorn into the\r\nmash, then barrel ageing in fresh\r\nbourbon barrels', '["Crispy bacon on flat bread","Glazed ham with crackling coating","Popcorn caramel and chocolate cake"]'),
(110, 110, 'WAIMEA', 'IPA is Dead', 'FEBRUARY 2013', 'Single Hop India Pale Ale.', '', 'Waimea has a new world flavour, infusing unique fresh crushed citrus aroma and flavour notes into this IPA - think intense fresh tangelo, citrus fruit and pine needle characteristics. There is a huge depth of flavour with astringent gooseberry balanced against the robust malt base.', '', 'Use the freshest hops for the most impact.', '', 20, 25, 6.7, 1015, 1066, 30, 15, 4.4, 77.3, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Hot spiced barbecue chicken wings","Orange sesame chicken","Chocolate fondue with fruit",""]'),
(11, 11, 'EDGE', '', 'DECEMEBER 2007', 'DARK FULL-BODIED CASK ALE.', '', 'Low ABV, high flavour, this beer was brewed to show that a beer can have all the flavour without the drunken affects. Also this beer is one of BrewDog''s original brews that made a rare appearance in cask. Spicy, malty biscuit and super drinkable.', '', 'Don’t overcook the mash - 75 minutes only at 65°C to get the right amount of fermentable sugars. Leave it too long and the beer ends up really watery and unpleasant.', '', 20, 25, 2.7, 1010, 1033, 57, 29, 4.4, 70.8, 36, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Lamb and root vegetable stew","Warm goats cheese salad","Raisin rum cake",""]'),
(108, 108, 'EL DORADO', 'IPA is Dead', 'FEBRUARY 2013', 'Single Hop India Pale Ale.', '', 'The Pacific North West of America grows remarkable hops and El Dorado is a killer example of this. A new hop on the block, loaded with tropical fruits, pear, watermelon, candy floss and stone fruit.', '', 'El Dorado works well on its own but pairs up brilliantly with a higher alpha hop for bittering, saving your El Dorado for aroma and flavour.', '', 20, 25, 6.7, 1015, 1066, 30, 15, 4.4, 77.3, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Watermelon and feta salad with balsamic reduction","Grilled chicken with a chilli soy sauce marinade","Crème brûlée with apricot coulis"]'),
(109, 109, 'GOLDINGS', 'IPA is Dead', 'FEBRUARY 2013', 'Single Hop India Pale Ale.', '', 'This is East Kent Goldings re- invented and re-imagined and shows just what can be done with English hops if you use enough of them. In this amped up Goldings reincarnation expect to be slammed with floral lavender, a fruity riot of blackberries and spiced pears, bubblegum, plums and the illusion of thyme.', '', 'Take a read through each year''s hop harvest that is available. Some years are better than others.', '', 20, 25, 6.7, 1015, 1066, 30, 15, 4.4, 77.3, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Rosemary and thyme marinated venison","Fish and chips","Lavender chocolate chip cookies",""]'),
(106, 106, 'AB:14', '', 'FEBRUARY 2013', 'oak-aged imperial Weizenbock.', '', 'Think banoffee pie; loads of creamy sweet banana, and sticky warm toffee. This beer is super complex, and one for the sweet-toothed!', '', 'Boil for even longer to get more caramelised flavours in the beer.', '', 20, 25, 10, 1016, 1094, 20, 10, 4.4, 83, 30, 0, '{"65":120}', '23', 'Oak chips 25g End', '["Sweet pork Chinese dumplings","Caramelised onion venison burger","Banoffee pie",""]'),
(107, 107, 'DANA', 'IPA is Dead', 'FEBRUARY 2013', 'Single Hop India Pale Ale.', '', 'Hailing from Slovenia, Dana was originally cross bred from the German Hallertau Magnum and native Slovenian varieties. Like any good faux noble hop should, it infuses a rustic, musty spiciness into a toasty beast of a malt base.', '', 'Noble hops (and their offspring) have a fundamentally different profile to many other hops, down to their different oil fractions. Chill your hops to retain all of the spicy, delicate volatile hop oils!', '', 20, 25, 6.7, 1015, 1066, 30, 15, 4.4, 77.3, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Spicy Asian-style noodles","Smokey chipotle beef brisket tostada","Sweet potato pie",""]'),
(105, 105, 'LICHTENSTEIN PALE ALE', '', 'JANUARY 2013', 'US-HOPPED RYE PALE ALE.', '', 'Dry-hopped with some of our hop heroes, bringing incredibly fruity aromas of zesty orange, pithy grapefruit, pungent pine and resin, backed up with spicy, toasty malt flavours of toffee, biscuit, rye bread and toast crust.', '', 'Munich malt adds a biscuit sweetness, while the rye adds a spicy bready character.', '', 20, 25, 5.2, 1010, 1050, 17, 8.5, 4.4, 80, 50, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Spicy fish tacos","Bacon mac ''n'' cheese","Pear crumble",""]'),
(104, 104, 'AMARILLO', 'IPA IS DEAD', 'JANUARY 2013', 'SINGLE HOP INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'Citrus fruit. Lots of citrus fruit. Think blood orange, orange zest and grapefruit, tangerine and lemon; the fruit is balanced by floral notes in the most classic of new wave IPA hops. Amarillo adds a zesty, pithy character that sits beautifully alongside hints of toffee and honeycomb.', '', 'Use the freshest hops for the most impact. It seems obvious but in a single hop beer, you want the hops to be at their best.', '', 20, 25, 7.2, 1012, 1067, 30, 15, 4.4, 82.1, 70, 0, '{"65":0}', '19', '', '["Bratwurst sausage with spicy mustard","Fried American bacon with chilli flakes added to the top","Dark chocolate chip cookies",""]'),
(102, 102, 'NUNS WITH GUNS', '', 'NOVEMBER 2012', 'DRY-HOPPED LAGER.', '', 'A dry-hopped Session Pilsner. At 4.2% this amber-hued lager packs a malty punch with toasty Munich character and a light caramel sweetness. From here, things take a sharp turn towards the hoppy flavour, with some serious US citrus packed classic hops.', '', 'Keep the temperature of the fermentation as close to 12ËC  as possible (or below). This allows the yeast to create a crisper and cleaner beer.', '', 20, 25, 4.2, 1012, 1044, 19, 9.5, 4.4, 72.7, 25, 0, '{"70":0}', '16', '', '["Falafel and hummus pitta wrap","Bratwurst with spicy relish","Strawberry tart"]'),
(103, 103, 'CATHERINE''S PONY', '(W/BEAVERTOWN)', 'DECEMBER 2012', 'IMPERIAL SMOKED PORTER - BEAVERTOWN COLLAB.', '', 'An Imperial Smoked Porter with a nose like gooseberries and blueberries, stuffed with coffee, covered in chocolate and toasted on a campfire by the beach, Catherineэs Pony is robust and imposing with a herculean mouthfeel. Rich and smooth with roasted smoky flavours battling for prominence over the assertive bitterness. A satisfying hoppiness rounds off the palate.', '', 'The smoke aroma comes from a mix of the Carafa malt and smoked malt. If you can''t get hold of fresh smoked malt - make your own in a barbeque - carefully!', '', 20, 25, 8.8, 1017, 1084, 190, 95, 4.5, 79.8, 40, 0, '{"67":90}', '21', 'Coffee End Flavour', '["Flame grilled steak","Venison and Winter vegetable stew","Maple bacon chocolate cupcakes",""]');
INSERT INTO `beers` (`beer_id`, `brand_id`, `beer_name`, `beer_subname`, `beer_since`, `beer_title`, `beer_subtitle`, `beer_description`, `beer_article`, `beer_tips`, `beer_collaboration`, `basics_volume`, `basics_boil_volume`, `basics_abv`, `basics_target_fg`, `basics_target_og`, `basics_ebc`, `basics_srm`, `basics_ph`, `basics_attenuation_level`, `heading_ibu`, `heading_abv`, `method_mash_temp`, `method_fermentation`, `method_twist`, `food_parings`) VALUES
(101, 101, 'COCOA PSYCHO', '', 'NOVEMBER 2012', 'RUSSIAN IMPERIAL STOUT.', 'RICH. DECADENT. MOCHA.', 'Vanilla pods and toasted oak chips add a rounded character to this massive Russian Imperial Stout, brewed with a hefty malt bill, cacao nibs and coffee beans. Dark malts combine with Cascade to add a punchy bitterness, strong enough to offset the big chocolate sweetness.', '', 'Put coffee beans and cocoa nibs in a cheese cloth and dip in wort like a tea bag. Do multiple small additions for short lengths of time - the longer you leave them in the more heavy oils will be extracted.', '', 20, 25, 10, 1012, 1098, 296, 150, 4.4, 70, 85, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', 'Coffee Beans 25g End\r\nCocoa Nibs 25g End\r\nCocoa Nibs 25g Conditioning\r\nCoffee Beans 25g Conditioning\r\nOak Chips 15g Conditioning', '["Smokey sweet pulled brisket","Espresso crusted venison with a dark cherry jus","Affogato with vanilla ice cream",""]'),
(10, 10, 'BUZZ', '', 'SEPTEMBER 2007', 'A REAL BITTER EXPERIENCE.', '', 'A light, crisp and bitter IPA brewed with English and American hops. A small batch brewed only once.', '', 'The earthy and floral aromas from the hops can be overpowering. Drop a little Cascade in at the end of the boil to lift the profile with a bit of citrus.', '', 20, 25, 4.5, 1010, 1044, 20, 10, 4.4, 75, 60, 0, '{"64":75}', '19', '', '["Spicy chicken tikka masala","Grilled chicken quesadilla","Caramel toffee cake",""]'),
(100, 100, 'BLACK EYED KING IMP', '', 'NOVEMBER 2012', 'BARREL-AGED PROTOTYPE COCOA PSYCHO.', '', 'An early Cocoa Psycho recipe that we loved, but didn''t fit what we were looking for. We locked this chocolate coffee stout away in barrels for two years, imparting toasted marshmallow, spicy vanilla, molasses and boozy warmth.', '', 'There is a huge amount of roasted malts in this grist. Be careful not to pulverise the malt into powder during the milling process.', '', 20, 25, 9.5, 1022, 1095, 250, 125, 4.4, 76.8, 85, 0, '{"65":50}', '18', 'Coffee Beans 12.5g End\r\nLactose 125g', '["Beef chilli made with cocoa powder","Dark chocolate covered bacon","Rich espresso tiramisu"]'),
(15, 15, 'ORIGINAL DOGMA', '(Née SPEEDBALL)', '', 'STRONG ALE WITH HONEY AND SPICES.', '', 'A strong ale, brewed with guarana, \r\nCalifornian poppy, kola nut and \r\nScottish heather honey. A conspiracy \r\nof trans-continental ingredients \r\ninfused with some devastatingly \r\nBrewDog imaginative thinking.', '', 'Get really good quality heather honey, \r\nthe more aromatic the better. Honey is \r\n100% fermentable, but it does have a huge \r\ninfluence on the ester profile of the beer – \r\nin this case high floral esters.', '', 20, 25, 7.8, 1012, 1071.3, 31, 15.5, 4.3, 83.2, 60, 0, '{"64":75}', '21', 'Herb and honey addition', '["Spicy seafood stew","French onion soup","Mexican wedding cake (cookies)"]'),
(25, 25, 'HOW TO DISAPPEAR COMPLETELY', '', '', 'FAKE FIX DOUBLE IPA.', '', 'Jam-packed with two of our \r\nfavourite hops - Columbus \r\nand Centennial, it has 198 (yes \r\none hundred and ninety eight) \r\ntheoretical IBUs. We use a lot of \r\ncaramalt, some amber malt and some \r\nchocolate malt to give the little \r\nbeer as much body and mouthfeel \r\nas possible and the ability to handle \r\nall the hops we threw at it. We think \r\nthis beer is the world’s first ever \r\nImperial Mild. Imperial in terms of \r\nhop profile. An Imperially Hopped \r\nMild. BrewDog’s Imperial Mild. \r\nHow to Disappear Completely.', '', 'Dry Hopping: Columbus 37.5g, Centennial 37.5g, Galena 37.5g, Horizon 37.5g', '', 20, 25, 3.5, 1010, 1037, 37, 19, 4.4, 73, 198, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Spicy pork sausages with red potato mash","Turnip beef stew with crusty fresh baked bread","Summer berry cheesecake"]'),
(51, 51, 'BLACK TOKYO HORIZON', '(W/NØGNE Ø & MIKKELLER)', '', 'Imperial Stout Collaboration.', '', 'Special Collaboration between\r\nNøgne, Mikkeller and BrewDog\r\nwhich is a recipe based on all\r\nthree brewers’ big stouts; Nøgne Ø\r\nDark Horizon, Mikkeller Black and\r\nBrewDog Tokyo*.', '', 'Extend the mash time as much as possible\r\nto create maximum fermentable sugars.\r\nBoil for longer in the kettle to help\r\nevaporate off the water, and make the\r\nsugar concentration stronger.', '', 20, 25, 17.2, 1030, 1156, 128, 64, 4.4, 80.8, 75, 0, '{"65":120}', '21', '', '["Truffle oil filet mignon","Sweet sticky beef brisket","Chocolate and dark cherry fondant"]'),
(70, 70, 'OLD WORLD RUSSIAN IMPERIAL STOUT', '', '', 'RUSSIAN IMPERIAL STOUT.', '', 'This Old World Stout perfectly\r\nrecreates the export stouts of years\r\ngone by; brewed to imperial strength\r\nto avoid freezing during its journey\r\nacross the Baltic Sea to snowy\r\nMoscow. Full bodied with huge\r\nchocolate, coffee and roast flavours,\r\nthis imperial stout employs a variety\r\nof hops to add enough bitterness\r\nand hop complexity to balance the\r\nhuge malt sweetness and rich mocha\r\nand molasses flavours.', '', 'Add the chocolate malt after the mash\r\nis complete, at the start of sparging.\r\nThis will extract flavour and colour,\r\nbut will prevent the extraction of harsh\r\ntannins into the wort.', '', 20, 25, 9.5, 1014, 1075, 195, 97.5, 4.5, 81.3, 80, 0, '{"16":90}', '19', '', '["Seared steak with a peppercorn sauce","Strong blue cheese and oatcakes","Chocolate cheesecake"]'),
(92, 92, 'SAN DIEGO SCOTCH ALE', '(W/BALLAST POINT)', '', 'IMPERIAL SCOTCH ALE WITH RUM & RAISIN.', '', 'Whisky cask aged with raisins soaked\r\nin rum. Warm, chocolatey and boozy\r\nwith refreshing resinous bitterness\r\nand a lingering toasty biscuit\r\nbackground from the malt. Toasted\r\noak comes courtesy of the barrels\r\nand spicy, sweet, dark fruit flavours\r\nfrom the rum soaked raisins.', '', 'Soak oak chips in rum, then steep in the\r\nbeer for the rum cash finish.', '', 20, 25, 9, 1018, 1090, 190, 95, 4.4, 80, 70, 0, '{"65":50}', '21', 'Age in whisky casks with rum\r\nsoaked raisins', '["Venison stroganoff","Chilli dog","Toffee chocolate cheesecake"]'),
(95, 95, 'INTERNATIONAL ARMS RACE', '(W/FLYING DOG)', '', 'ZERO IBU HERBAL IPA.', '', 'The International Arms Race was\r\na new type of battle collaboration\r\nbetween hardcore American craft\r\nbrewery Flying Dog and BrewDog.\r\nBoth breweries attempted to brew\r\nan IPA with absolutely no hops.', '', 'Allow the bay leaves to steep in the boil\r\nfor extra time to extract some bitterness.\r\nThe bitterness is really important to bring\r\nbalance to an otherwise sweet beer.', '', 20, 25, 7.5, 1013, 1069, 50, 25, 4.4, 81.1, 0, 0, '{"69":0}', '19', 'Juniper Berries 25g Start\r\nBay Leaves 2.75g Start\r\nRosemary 7.5g Start\r\nRosemary 5g End\r\nElderflower 15g End\r\nJuniper Berries 25g End', '["Rosemary and thyme grilled chicken","Light vegetable and herb soup with toasted rye bread","Earl Grey ice cream with a lavender sauce"]'),
(122, 122, 'HELLO MY NAME IS METTE-MARIT', '', '', 'LINGONBERRY DOUBLE IPA.', '', 'We sent this beer to Norway where\r\nit was known as ''Hello, my name is\r\nCensored’. You can make up your\r\nown mind as to why. This brew was a\r\nred berry explosion, with a reisnous\r\nbitter edge layered with dry berry\r\ntartness.', '', 'Using crushed cranberries will dry out\r\nthe beer further, drawing out their natural\r\nastringent character.', '', 20, 25, 8.2, 1013, 1076, 0, 0, 4.4, 83, 70, 0, '{"66":90}', '19', 'Infusion of lingonberries alongside\r\nthe dry hops\r\nCranberry juice 5.5g 30mins\r\nLingonberries 10g Twist', '["F\\u00e5rik\\u00e5l (mutton stew) with a spicy twist","Fenal\\u00e5r (salted cured lamb)","Krumkake with lingonberry jam"]'),
(127, 127, 'HELLO MY NAME IS SONJA', '(W/EVIL TWIN)', '', 'BLUEBERRY DOUBLE IPA.', '', 'Brewed in collaboration with Jeppe\r\nfrom Evil Twin Brewing (and named\r\nafter his mum), this Double IPA is big\r\non fruity flavours.\r\nSingle hopped with Mosaic for lots\r\nof tropical, passion fruit and citrus\r\nflavours. Loaded with well over\r\n100kg of blueberries, the original was\r\none super fruity hop bomb.', '', 'Mash the blueberries before adding to\r\nthe kettle. This will help with flavour\r\nextraction and turning your wort a nice\r\nshade of purple.', '', 20, 25, 8.3, 1013, 1076, 30, 15, 4.4, 82.9, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', '', '["Lamb chops with a blueberry reduction","Cured ham and strong mulled cheddar board","Warm blueberry pie"]'),
(128, 128, 'SHIPWRECKER CIRCUS', '(W/OSKAR BLUES)', '', 'AMERICAN BARLEY WINE - OSKAR BLUES COLLAB.', '', 'In collaboration with the awesome\r\nOskar Blues from Colorado, we\r\ncreated this big, twisted 10.5%\r\nAmerican style barley wine. Big\r\nboozy aromas and a sweet viscosity,\r\npacked in with some heavy-hitting\r\nC-hops, for an intense bitterness\r\nto balance this full-bodied malt\r\nmonster.', '', 'Age this beer in the cellar for a few months\r\nto allow the warm alcohol flavours to\r\nreduce.', '', 20, 25, 10.5, 1022, 1102, 64, 32, 4.4, 102, 85, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', '', '["Stilton","Pan seared steak","Dark chocolate fondant"]'),
(156, 156, 'MAGIC STONE DOG', '(W/MAGIC ROCK & STONE BREWING CO.)', '', 'SESSION FARMHOUSE IPA - STONE / MAGIC ROCK COLLAB.', '', 'A session IPA brewed with a diverse\r\ngrain bill, hopped with Simcoe\r\nand Amarillo and fermented with\r\nsaison yeast, for an incredible level\r\nof depth in a low ABV beer. Spicy,\r\nfruity, complex, refreshing and dry.', '', 'Start the fermentation off at 20˚C and\r\nallow it to rise as high as 25˚C . This will\r\nincrease the fruity character of the yeast.', '', 20, 25, 4.6, 1008, 1043, 15, 7.5, 4.4, 81.4, 30, 0, '{"65":75}', '23', 'Cumin 0.5g End\r\nCaraway 1g End\r\nPeppercorns\r\n(Pink)\r\n5g End\r\nGrains of\r\nParadise\r\n5g End', '["Halibut with caper brown butter","Creamy gorgonzola and satsuma salad","Spicy Daal with garlic naan bread"]'),
(173, 173, 'SHAREHOLDER BREW - BOUNTY HUNTER', '', '', 'BEATNIK MILK STOUT.', '', 'Brewed with our Equity Punks this\r\nrich, smooth stout is brewed with\r\na blend of six malts, resulting in a\r\nwelcoming, resonant black beer.\r\nFrom start to finish it carries an\r\nintense roastiness reminiscent of\r\ndark chocolate intertwined with\r\na delicate hint of coconut and\r\ncaramel.', '', 'Lightly toast the coconut chips to allow\r\nbetter interaction with the hot wort.', '', 20, 25, 6.5, 1020, 1068, 250, 125, 4.2, 70.6, 35, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', 'Cacao Nibs 25g End\r\nCoconut Chips 20g End\r\nLactose (wk) 375g End\r\nCoconut Chips 50g FV', '["Coconut beef red curry","Butternut squash soup with toasted almonds","Chocolate coated macaroons"]'),
(174, 174, 'RESTORATIVE BEVERAGE FOR INVALIDS AND CONVALESCENTS', '', '', 'AN EXTRACT TAKEN FROM "A TREATISE ON FOOD AND DIET" BY DR JONATHAN PEREIRA, 1843.', '', 'Brewed to 8.5%, light as a mass\r\nmarket Pilsner in colour, fermented\r\nto be as dry as a Lambic, but as\r\nbitter as any double IPA and loaded\r\nwith as much hop aroma as we can\r\nget into a beer. The fermentables in\r\nthis beer were Marris Otter Extra\r\nPale along with plenty of sugar as we\r\nmashed at a very low temperature to\r\nensure maximum fermentability and\r\nattenuation. This beer is fermented\r\nwithin an inch of its life making it\r\ndry, sheer and bright. Citra, Amarillo\r\n& Centennial were all used in\r\nabundance in the kettle and also\r\nfired extremely liberally at this beer\r\nwith our high tech hop cannon.', '', 'Allow the mash to sit at lower\r\ntemperatures for an extended period to\r\nconvert the maximum amount of starch to\r\nfermetable sugars. This will give the beer a\r\nhigher ABV and dry it out.', '', 20, 25, 8.5, 1003, 1068, 15, 7.5, 4.4, 95.6, 101, 0, '{"63":90}', '21', '', '["Habanero spicy chicken wings with ranch sauce","Jalape\\u00f1o chilli and chicken quesadillas","New York style cheesecake"]'),
(178, 178, 'HELLO MY NAME IS LITTLE INGRID', '', '', 'CLOUDBERRY SESSION IPA.', '', 'This beer hits all the high-points\r\nof Hello My Name is Ingrid – with\r\none important exception. Brewed at\r\n4.4% abv, Little Ingrid is a sessionstrength\r\nversion of our cloudberryinfused\r\ncelebration of all that is epic\r\nabout Sweden. The zesty balance of\r\ncitrus from the four different hops is\r\njust as pronounced as in the original.', '', 'Sourcing fresh cloudberries might involve a\r\ntrip to Sweden but boy are they worth it.', '', 20, 25, 4.4, 1012, 1045, 30, 15, 4.4, 73.3, 35, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', 'Cloudberries 27.5g End', '["Scones with cloudberry jam","Oysters with a chilli and dill sauce","Rhubarb tart"]'),
(181, 181, 'MANDARINA BAVARIA', 'IPA IS DEAD', '', 'SINGLE HOP INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'From the central European plains\r\nof Germany, comes something very\r\ndifferent. A blast of tangerine and\r\norange, Mandarina Bavaria brings\r\na highly distinctive backbone of\r\nflavour. This is down to its parent –\r\nCascade – and a frankly enormous\r\n70% myrcene oil content. If equate\r\nGermany solely with earthy, spicy\r\nNoble hops, Mandarina Bavaria will\r\nmake you think again.', '', 'We''ve mentioned the importance of\r\nfresh hops previously but this one really\r\ndemands that your hops are the absolute\r\nfreshest.', '', 20, 25, 7.2, 1010, 1064, 12, 6, 4.4, 84, 100, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Lavender and thyme roast beef","Spicy kung po chicken","Caramel and rose essence cheesecake"]'),
(184, 184, 'B-SIDES - MELON AND CUCUMBER IPA', '', '', 'FRESH MELON IPA.', '', 'A Pilot Brew with 200Kg of fresh\r\nmelon and 5Kg fresh cucumber\r\nadded after fermentation to produce\r\nthe perfect summer refreshment.', '', 'Have a good food proccesser to blend up\r\nall the melon and cucumber, also sieve out\r\nthe seeds from the melon.', '', 20, 25, 6, 1010, 1050, 8, 4, 5.2, 87, 50, 0, '{"60":10}', '20', 'Melon 500g\r\nCucumber 20g', '["Beef carpaccio","Chilled beetroot soup","Korean watermelon salad"]'),
(186, 186, 'B-SIDES - TRUFFLE AND CHOCOLATE STOUT', '', '', 'Gastronomic session stout.', '', 'Pilot Brew - Truffle & Chocolate\r\nStout. Deep, earthy roast notes\r\nmake this a gastronome''s dream.', '', 'A little truffle goes a long way. Add 5g,\r\nleave for a 2 days and add more if needed.', '', 20, 25, 5.6, 1015, 1058, 54, 27, 4.4, 74, 30, 0, '{"60":10}', '19', 'Use Perigold Truffles after\r\nfermentation', '["Mushroom pithivier","Roast pheasant with savoy cabbage","Dark chocolate ganache macaroons"]'),
(189, 189, 'B-SIDES - SPICED CHERRY SOUR', '', '', 'ALTERNATIVE FESTIVE.', '', 'Think bakewell tart with Christmas\r\nspices.', '', 'In the boil: cinnamon, star anise, clove,\r\nguinea pepper.\r\nAfter fermentation add: raspberry puree,\r\ncherry concentrate, bitter almond extract,\r\nAmerican oak chips and Tahitian vanilla\r\nbeans.', '', 20, 25, 6.5, 1010, 1060, 0, 0, 3.2, 87, 20, 0, '{"60":10}', '20', '', '["Wild rice salad with wild mushrooms","Apple gingerbread pancakes","Christmas Pudding"]'),
(195, 195, 'HELLO MY NAME IS HOLY MOOSE', '', '', 'Nordic berry ipa.', '', 'Cloudberry, lingonberry, blueberry\r\nand sea buckthorn meld with citrusy\r\nhops in an intensely sweet, fruity\r\nand floral aroma, with toasty malt\r\nnotes and tropical fruit bursts. This\r\nbitter, resinous IPA follows up with a\r\nlemony punch in the mouth - cherry\r\nand blueberry sourness takes this\r\npithy pale ale in a new direction\r\nbefore a long, dry finish.', '', 'The mixture of berries and hops create a\r\nvery intense flavour profile, a great brew\r\nfor using up some spare hops.', '', 20, 25, 5.5, 1011, 1053, 25, 12.5, 4.4, 79.3, 35, 0, '{"65":0}', '17', 'Lingon Berries 25g End\r\nCloudberries 25g End\r\nBlueberry\r\nConcentrate\r\n62.5g FV\r\nSea Buckthorn 62.5g FV', '["Warms goats cheese salad","Trifle or chocolate cake"]'),
(206, 206, 'INDIA SESSION LAGER', 'PROTOTYPE CHALLENGE', '', 'REFESHING HOP FIX.', '', 'BrewDog’s level of dry-hop to a beer\r\nformed with a baseline of 100%\r\npilsner malt – and at under 4.5%\r\nABV – gives you a style that flirts at\r\nthe edges of several others. Think\r\naromas of fresh cut grass, nettle,\r\nwhite grape, melon, tangerine - with\r\nsimilar flavours leading to a dry,\r\nbitter finish.', '', 'Let the beer lager at a low temperature for\r\n3-4 weeks before adding the dry hops.', '', 20, 25, 4.4, 1007, 1040, 12, 6, 4.4, 79.5, 35, 0, '{"65":75}', '10', '', '["Tomato and rosemary palmiers","Bratwurst with sauerkraut","Lemon drizzle cake"]'),
(207, 207, 'HOPPED-UP BROWN ALE', 'PROTOTYPE CHALLENGE', '', 'Malt hop balance.', '', 'Brown ales are perfect foils for\r\nresinous C-Hops, as the piney\r\nelements of the latter contrast\r\nbrilliantly with the sweeter,\r\nnutty elements of the malt bill.\r\nThe best of both worlds.', '', 'High carbonate water will really accent\r\nthe malt notes to better balance the\r\npunchy hops.', '', 20, 25, 6.3, 1015, 1063, 24, 12, 4.2, 82.6, 85, 0, '{"65":0}', '19', '', '["Butternut squash and sage soup","Roast beef and horseradish sandwich","Fudge"]'),
(209, 209, 'B-SIDES - BERLINER WEISSE WITH RASPBERRIES AND RHUBARB', '', '', 'Fruity Berliner Weisse.', '', 'Tart, dry and acidic with a punch of\r\nsummer berry as rhubarb crumble.', '', 'Fruits added at the end of the boil for 10\r\nmins and additional added in maturation.\r\nBoil for no more than 15 mins.', '', 20, 25, 3.6, 1007, 1040, 0, 0, 3.2, 83, 8, 0, '{"60":10}', '21', 'Raspberries in the boil, rhubarb at\r\nmaturation. Soured naturally using\r\nthe kettle souring technique\r\nRaspberries Middle', '["Grilled salmon","Mac and cheese fries","Cheesecake with raspberry coulis"]'),
(212, 212, 'B-SIDES - BERLINER WEISSE WITH YUZU', '', '', 'Japanese Citrus Berliner Weisse.', '', 'Japanese citrus fruit intensifies the\r\nsour nature of this German classic.', '', 'Clean everything twice. All you want is\r\nthe clean sourness of lactobacillus.', '', 20, 25, 4.2, 1007, 1040, 8, 4, 3.2, 83, 8, 0, '{"60":10}', '21', 'Soured naturally using the kettle\r\nsouring technique\r\nYuzu fruit 50g Middle\r\nYuzu juice 200ml FV', '["Smoked chicken wings","Miso ramen","Yuzu cheesecake"]'),
(213, 213, 'B-SIDES - CASCADE, CENTENNIAL & WILLAMETTE IPA', '', '', 'Pilot Kit ipa.', '', 'An experiment in balancing hops on\r\nthe pilot kit. Grapefruit, orange and\r\nresin to the fore.', '', 'Hold off on the dry hops. You want to\r\nknow how well you balanced the brew\r\nhouse.', '', 20, 25, 6.4, 1011, 1060, 14, 7, 5.2, 82, 65, 0, '{"60":10}', '19', '', '["Cauliflower pakora with mango chutney","Penne with tomato and smoked cheese","Salted caramel ice cream and peanuts"]'),
(214, 214, 'B-SIDES - SINGLE HOP ENIGMA IPA', '', '', 'Enigma Hopped IPA.', '', 'A cheeky play with a new hop on the\r\npilot kit. Expect notes of redcurrant,\r\nmelon and citrus. An intriguing\r\npossibility for the future.', '', 'Enigma has a very high alpha acid so be\r\ncareful not to over do the bittering hops.', '', 20, 25, 5, 1011, 1050, 10, 5, 4.4, 78, 50, 0, '{"60":10}', '19', '', '["Jalape\\u00f1o poppers with blue cheese dip","T-bone steak with fried onions","Carrot cake with cream cheese frosting"]'),
(224, 224, 'BARREL AGED ALBINO SQUID ASSASSIN', '', '', 'RED RYE IPA AGED IN RYE WHISKY CASK.', '', 'This tentacled terminator packs a\r\npunch - ten punches to be precise.\r\nEach hop addition adds to the\r\nintense layers of depth in this red\r\nrye IPA. Toasty caramel & cinder\r\ntoffee from crystal malts, cacao\r\nrichness from intensely roasted\r\nmalt and the spiciness of rye. Zesty\r\npithiness from Citra and the robust\r\nresin of Chinook. This small batch\r\nexclusive brew is up-front intensity\r\nmatched with twisted complexity.\r\nAged in Rye Whisky Casks.', '', '20% specialty malts in this grist can\r\ncreate problems in the run off. Be careful\r\nnot to pull the bed down onto the plates.', '', 20, 25, 9.2, 1012, 1069, 60, 30, 4.2, 82.6, 65, 0, '{"65":0}', '18', '', '["Rocket and mozzarella salad with a cracked pepper dressing","Fried halibut with sweet potato fritters","Grapefruit and blood orange tart"]'),
(235, 225, 'KINGPIN', '', '', '21ST CENTURY LAGER.', '', 'A 4.7% German Pils with light, biscuit and toasty malt character, upon which is built a hop bitterness that provides complexity and a long, dry finish.', '', 'Keep an eye on your fermentation temperature to ensure you get the crisp notes that are the hallmark of a good pilsner.', '', 20, 25, 4.7, 1008, 1044, 14, 7, 4.2, 79, 40, 0, '{"65":75}', '10', '', '["Jamaican jerk chicken wings","Corn dogs","Strawberry ice cream sundae",""]'),
(236, 228, '#MASHTAG 2016', '', '', 'SOUR CHERRY TRIPLE IPA.', '', 'We gave our customers the keys to the brewery and let them choose every aspect of this beer. Sour cherry combines with fruity hop character against a biscuit malt backbone with a hint of alcohol warmth, and an oaky undercurrent.\r\n', '', 'Rope in as many friends as you can to make it a truly democratic brew.', '', 20, 25, 10.5, 1010, 1090, 15, 8, 4.4, 89.04, 100, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', '250g Sour Cherries\r\n5g Oak Chips', '["Confit duck with cherry sauce","Cajun ribs","Buttermilk waffles"]'),
(237, 237, 'MANGO AND CHILI BARLEY WINE', '', '2016', 'SPICY, CHEWY, SWEET.', '', 'A huge, chewy barley wine, loaded with bitterness and balanced with a sweet and spicy combo of mango and chili. A concept brew which was so well received, we tweaked it and it became Neon Overlord.', '', 'Crack open the chili and add it in a muslin bag so you can take it out when the chilli heat suits you.', '', 20, 25, 12, 1015, 1110, 20, 40, 4.4, 84, 50, 0, '{"60":30}', '21', 'Coriander Seed 4 Whirlpool Aroma\r\nMango 500 Secondary Flavour \r\n1 lemon  drop chilli n/a Maturation Flavour\r\n', '["Vegetable Samosas","Thai Green Chicken Curry","Vanilla Panna Cotta"]'),
(238, 238, 'SCIENCE IPA', '', '2016', 'INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'A beer brewed specifically for the British Science Festival, held in Swansea.', '', 'This beer is all about the balance between the malty backbone of the beer and the fresh hop aroma. The fresher the hops  the better.', '', 20, 25, 5, 1011, 1050, 24, 47, 4.4, 77, 45, 0, '{"60":30}', '21', '', '["Chicken Katsu","Cheese and Ham Omelette","Pumpkin Pie"]'),
(239, 239, 'HONEY AND LEMON BLITZ', '', '2016', 'HONEY & LEMON INFUSED BERLINER WEISSE.', '', 'Honey & Lemon Blitz sees tart Berliner Weisse character multiplied by lemony acidity; light bready malt and a hint of warming honey hold this back from the brink of palatedestroying sourness.\r\n', '', 'Be careful not to over do the smoked malt as it’s just a background flavour and you  don’t want it to be prominent in the finished beer.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 3.2, 1008, 1039, 8, 4, 3.2, 75, 8, 0, '{"60":30}', '21', '', '["Herb-Crusted Baked Cod","Berry and Cream Meringue","Lemon Drizzle Cake",""]'),
(240, 240, 'BLITZ SAISON', '', '2016', 'LEMON & CORIANDER BERLINER WEISSE.', '', 'Belgium meets Berlin – incredible saison character with a bright and vibrant sour edge.\r\n', '', 'This will ferment out very dry due to the yeast.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 3.2, 1007, 1040, 7, 14, 3.2, 77, 8, 0, '{"60":30}', '21', '', '["Taleggio and Spinach Tart","Chicken Adobo","Cr\\u00e8me Caramel",""]'),
(241, 241, 'HELLO MY NAME IS INGRID', '', '2016', 'CLOUDBERRY DOUBLE IPA.', '', 'We asked the public to tell us the one beer we should brew again, from our entire back catalogue. They chose well. Cloudberries team up with pan-global hops for an all out fruit riot against a caramel malt base.\r\n', '', 'Add the cloudberries to your beer when racking the beer after primary fermentation. Grind them into a paste to allow maximum flavour extraction.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 8.2, 1013, 1076, 30, 15.2, 5.2, 83.3, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', '', '["Tempura Prawns","Soy-Glazed Chicken Thighs","Raspberry Souffl\\u00e9",""]'),
(242, 242, 'CREW BREW', '', '2016', 'DEMOCRATIC AMBER ALE.', '', 'Our crew designed it, and we bottled it just for ourselves! We chose an 8% red ale, mash hopped and first wort hopped with New Zealand origin hops.\r\n', '', 'Bring a few bottles to your local BrewDog bar when it''s done and ask the staff if you got it right, they''re the only ones who can tell you for sure! They''ll also probably know of other homebrewers and beer enthusiasts nearby that you can link in with to share your experiences and get awesome first hand advice from.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 8, 1011, 1072, 28, 14.2, 5.2, 84.62, 100, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', '', '["Panko-coated Chicken Katsu","Classic Cheddar Ploughmans","Pecan Pie",""]'),
(243, 243, 'GIN BLITZ', '', '2016', 'BOTANICAL BERLINER WEISSE.', '', 'Our Blitz series sees us brew up low abv, super tart Berliner Weisse, and generally infuse them with bags of sour fruit flavour – but this batch uses gin botanicals instead.\r\n', '', 'Crack open/mash up the Juniper berries to get the most flavour and aroma from them. ', '', 20, 25, 3.2, 1008, 1038, 8, 4, 3.2, 75, 8, 0, '{"60":30}', '21', 'Kettle Soured\r\n', '["Game Terrine with Pickles","Fish Tacos","Peach Melba",""]'),
(244, 244, 'AB:21', '', '2016', 'LIQUORICE BLACKCURRANT STOUT.', '', 'AB:21 is a liquorice and blackcurrant infused imperial stout. Rolling in at an imposing 12% abv, this huge and decadent dark beer dials down the charred roastiness and focuses instead on the rich, full-bodied chocolate and dark fruit character of the style.\r\n', '', 'As with all of our Abstrakts this one is great for ageing. Be extra vigilant at all times as a small fault now will lead to disaster a few years down the line.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 12, 1015, 1130, 200, 101.6, 5.1, 82, 100, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', 'Liquorice\r\n200g Blackcurrant Concentrate FV', '["Steak Pie and Winter Vegetables","Chocolate Torte","Blackcurrant Panna Cotta",""]'),
(245, 245, 'BEATNIK', '', '2016', 'IMPERIAL RED ALE.', '', 'We gave our Equity Punks the keys to the brewery and let them brew the beer, as well as join Q&As and tour our HQ. The beer was voted on exclusively by Equity Punks.\r\n', '', 'For a real authentic experience invite all of your friends around to help on brewday. Try splitting the batch up after primary fermentation and dry hopping at different rates to see which you prefer. You can also blend the different versions back together to see how that tastes, have fun with it!\r\n', '', 20, 25, 8, 1013, 1075, 60, 30.5, 5.2, 83.78, 60, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Loaded Hamburger and Spicy Fries","Warm Banana Bread","Pineapple Sponge Cake",""]'),
(246, 246, 'CASINO RYE ALE', '', '2016', 'LIFE''S A GAMBLE.', '', 'We’ve split our bets with Casino Rye Ale and doubled up on the malt front, with barley and rye on the grain bill.\r\n', '', 'We don''t recommend roulette as a way to design beer. Spin the bottle is a much more sensible option. Make this beer with the freshest ingredients you can. Try to arrange brewday as close to delivery day as possible and throw 10 brewbucks on black 17 for us.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 5.1, 1009, 1049, 25, 12.7, 5.2, 81.6, 40, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', '', '["Crab Cakes","Spicy Bean Burrito","Dundee Fruit Cake",""]'),
(247, 247, 'SELF ASSEMBLY POPE', '', '2016', 'COCONUT VANILLA PORTER.', '', 'A dark and decadent beer brewed with coconut, vanilla, cacao.\r\n', '', 'Don''t be shy with the roasted coconut, it''s a delicate flavour compared to the rest of the beer, so go nuts! If it grows wild near you, go grab some Gorse and chuck it in too for a local natural boost to the coconut flavours.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 7.4, 1016, 1072, 200, 101.6, 5.1, 82, 75, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', 'Toasted Coconut Chips – 40g FV\r\nVanilla Extract – FV', '["Beef Rendang","Coconut Macaroons","Profiteroles with Chantilly Cream",""]'),
(248, 248, 'TWIN ATLANTIC', '', '2016', 'MANGO & PINEAPPLE PALE.', '', 'Brewed in collaboration with our AGM-headlining band, Twin Atlantic, this US style pale features some of our favourite hops and is loaded with tropical fruit.\r\n', '', 'If you can''t find an awesome Scottish band to collaborate with just pump up the volume on your stereo and have fun moshing whilst you''re mashing in. Use ripe but fresh fruit and be prepared to lose extra volume to it. It''ll be worth it.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 5, 1011, 1048, 19, 9.7, 5.2, 77, 80, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', 'Mango and Pineapple added to FV after Primary fermentation\r\n', '["Jerk Chicken Kebabs with  Mango Salsa Avocado and Citrus Salad","Pineapple Upside Down Cake",""]'),
(249, 249, 'HOP SHOT', '', '2016', 'QUADRUPLE INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'Hop Shot is a high-velocity hop hit. Our latest experiment in icedistillation is a west coast IPA, subjected to Antarctic temperatures and concentrated by removing the ice that forms. The result is a 22% ABV hop grenade in a 110ml bottle.\r\n', '', 'This level of alcohol can be achieved using a domestic freezer. Use a container with a tap close to the bottom so you can run the un-frozen, concentrated beer from under the ice on top. You may have to do this three or four times. The colder you freeze it the boozier it gets. Be careful to not dilute it too much when draining off the concentrated liquid after freezing so you don’t dilute it too much', '', 20, 25, 7, 1010, 1065, 15, 7.5, 4.4, 85, 250, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Phall Curry","Pork Burrito with a Habanero and Mango Chili Salsa","Ginger and Grapefruit Poundcake",""]'),
(250, 250, 'RYE IPA', 'SMALL BATCH', '2016', 'RYE INDIA PALE ALE.', '', 'A 7.2% rye IPA loaded with grapefruit notes, pithy citrus, and huge resinous bitterness, with rye character. The Centennial and Columbus flavours are amplified by the spicy, dry rye.\r\n', '', 'Be prepared for a long sparge as the rye content is really high.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 7.2, 1010, 1065, 8, 16, 4.4, 84, 101, 0, '{"60":30}', '21', '', '["Salmon Fishcakes with Rocket Salad","Baked Goat''s Cheese","Classic Victoria Sponge",""]'),
(251, 251, 'SORACHI ACE SESSION', 'SMALL BATCH', '2016', 'SORACHI ACE BELGIAN PALE.', '', 'This brew is a pale ale fermented with Belgian yeast and spiced with coriander seed.\r\n', '', 'If you dry hop with extra Sorachi Ace you''ll end up with an awesome extra hit of lemony zing but be warned, it''ll go through a lot of interesting variations on the way, including coconut and even bubblegum! Give it time though and it''ll land back at that lovely lemon zest that will compliment the coriander seeds perfectly.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 4, 1005, 1035, 15, 7.62, 5.1, 79, 25, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', 'Crushed Coridaner Seeds – FV', '["Californian Roll Sushi","Parmesan and Rocket Pizza","Coconut Cake",""]'),
(252, 252, 'DORTMUNDER', 'SMALL BATCH', '2016', 'PALE LAGER.', '', 'A pale lager, with toasty biscuit malt balanced against a robust spicy bitterness.\r\n', '', 'To really nail this style you need to get the water right. Do a bit of research on water profiles and ask a local brewery if they can help you out with some water treatments.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 4.9, 1009, 1049, 15, 7.62, 5.2, 81.5, 32, 0, '{"65":75}', '14', '', '["Cajun Chicken Burger","Baked Brie","Tomato and Herb Bruschetta",""]'),
(253, 253, '90 SHILLING', 'SMALL BATCH', '2016', 'HONEYED SPICY MALT.', '', 'A malt-forward Scotch ale with a complex but mellow mix of toast crust, caramel, hints of cocoa, and a light hop spiciness.\r\n', '', 'Pre-mix your malts to keep the conversion of starches to sugars even across the mash and give you a more uniform grain bed for lautering and sparging. This is a lot less labour intensive than manually stirring your speciality malts into your mash tun.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 5.3, 1010, 1056, 40, 20.32, 4.2, 73, 25, 0, '{"54":75}', '19', '', '["Game Terrine","Barbecue-griddled Poussin","Clootie Dumpling",""]'),
(254, 254, 'KELLERBIER', 'SMALL BATCH', '2016', 'CRISP UNFILTERED GOODNESS.', '', 'A pale lager, with toasty biscuit malt balances against a robust spicy bitterness.\r\n', '', 'Kellerbier translates to cellar beer, if you don’t have a cellar just make sure to keep the fermentation temperature as close as possible to what you''d expect in a bavarian basement.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 4.5, 1011, 1043, 17, 8.6, 5.3, 79, 25, 0, '{"56":75}', '10', '', '["Bratwurst and Mustard","Caraway Roast Pork","Gingerbread Cake","",""]'),
(255, 255, 'TRIPEL', 'SMALL BATCH', '2016', 'SPICED BELGIUM ALE.', '', 'Intense spicy and citrusy notes backed up with a bitter edge and a warming but dry malt biscuit backbone. This beer comes into its own after cellaring cool for a few weeks.\r\n', '', 'Brew twice as much Belgian Tripel as you were planning on ageing - it''s awesome on its own too!\r\n', '', 20, 25, 13, 1008, 1110, 23, 11.6, 5.1, 93, 50, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', 'Bitter Orange  Peel 20 End Flavour\r\nOat Husks 40 End Flavour', '["Coriander & Chilli Crab Cakes","Basil Pasta","Caramelised Orange Cheesecake",""]'),
(256, 256, 'VERMONT IPA', 'SMALL BATCH', '2016', 'JUICY, TROPICAL, CITRUSY.', '', 'A vermont style IPA, with low background bitterness, loaded with intense juicy fruit character.\r\n', '', 'Add the dry hops in separate muslin bags to increase surface area contact and reduce the amount of hop matter in the beer after dry hopping without reducing the characteristic hazy look of the beer', '', 20, 25, 6.9, 1012, 1066, 15, 7.62, 4.2, 79, 35, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Chicken Korma","Lobster Tail Salad","Chickpea and Apricot Tagine",""]'),
(257, 257, 'SEMI SKIMMED OCCULTIST', '', '2016', 'OATMEAL MILK STOUT.', '', 'This one-off brew is packed with all the decadent flavours and textures associated with Imperial Stouts.  This can features exclusive artwork by The Red Dress.\r\n', '', 'Surface area contact is key in dry additions. Make sure your coffee and cacao nibs are weighed down with something and spread them out between multiple muslin bags if you can. This is not an exact science so taste as you go and swap out for fresh coffee and/or cacao if you haven''t gotten the flavour you want after five days or so. You will not have this problem with the vanilla.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 8, 1014, 1080, 160, 81.28, 4.1, 73, 70, 0, '{"65":75}', '18', 'Coffee 20g FV\r\nCacoa Nibs 20g FV\r\nVanilla 4g FV', '["Pan-Seared Venison with Blackberries Fig Tart","Dark Chocolate and Coffee Torte",""]'),
(258, 258, 'PARADOX RYE', '', '2016', 'RYE WHISKY BARREL-AGED IMPERIAL STOUT.', '', 'In 2006 James and Martin hijacked a beer dinner run by Michael Jackson, the acclaimed beer and whisky writer, and convinced him to taste one of their home brews. This was a defining moment in BrewDog prehistory, and that beer was the first incarnation of the ubiquitous Paradox. Aged in a variety of casks over the years, Paradox is dark, decadent and encapsulating.  Can be enjoyed fresh; phenomenal when aged.\r\n', '', 'The beauty of this beer is in how brilliantly it lends itself to infusing or ageing. Experiment with different additions when the beer is ageing, taste it regularly to gauge its progress, and make sure you package it at its peak.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 13, 1112, 1015, 300, 152, 4.4, 84, 100, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', 'Age this beer in Rye Whisky Casks', '["Char-grilled Lamb Cutlets","BBQ Brisket","Chocolate and Strawberry Mousse",""]'),
(259, 259, 'TROPIC THUNDER', '', '2016', 'ISLAND-HOPPING STOUT.', '', 'Tropic Thunder is the winner of the first ever #HomeBrewDog competition; the brainchild of Tom Doyle, this beer was the highest rated of the 307 beers that were tasted. A full-bodied and complex stout loaded with chocolate, mocha and roasty flavours, finishing with a vibrant burst of orange.', '', 'If you are feeling adventurous, and haven’t guzzled your whole batch upon first tasting it, try mulling this like you would a wine or cider. Cinnamon and clove will really lend themselves to the flavour of Tropic Thunder and mulled beer is definitely cooler than the usual offerings at a winter gathering.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 7, 1020, 1074, 170, 86.36, 4.2, 73, 25, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', 'Sweet Orange Peel  20g Whirlpool', '["Steak and Kidney Pie","Pork Carnitas","Chocolate Orange Brownies",""]'),
(260, 260, 'NEW ENGLAND IPA', '(W/CLOUDWATER)', '2016', 'VERMONT IPA.', '', 'BrewDog vs Cloudwater is a 6.8% Vermont-style India Pale Ale, hopped with Mosaic in the whirlpool only. Without any bighitting additions of hops in the boil, we carried the flavour by heavily dry-hopping the brew with Citra and Mosaic. We also used oats in the recipe to deliver the trademark smooth mouthfeel – and made it truly authentic by propagating a one-off culture of Vermont yeast, specifically for the brew.\r\n', '', 'Skip the arrageenan (Irish Moss), all haze is good haze in this beer.\r\n', '', 20, 25, 6.8, 1012, 1065, 17, 9, 4.2, 79, 25, 0, '{"68":75}', '18', '', '["Goat''s Cheese Bruschetta","Pan-Fried Lemon Sole","Baked Peaches with Citrus Fruit Reduction",""]'),
(261, 261, 'NITRO BREAKFAST STOUT', 'SMALL BATCH', '2016', 'BOOZY CHOCOLATE MILKSHAKE.', '', 'An utterly indulgent, smooth as hell Stout. With opulent flavours of chocolate milkshake, roasty espresso coffee, and mellow vanilla,  this beer has a full-bodied and creamy mouthfeel.', '', '*Not a suitable replacement for an  actual breakfast. Nitroing at home is, well, not impossible but unlikely. Luckily this beer tastes  great when lightly carbonated too!  Be prepared for a slow runoff and don’t skimp on the cacao!\r\n', '', 20, 25, 8, 1027, 1092, 88, 44.7, 5.2, 70, 80, 0, '{"65":75}', '21', 'Vanilla Extract 25g End\r\nCacao Nibs 25g End\r\nCoffee 25g End', '["Habanero Pulled Pork","Choc Chip Cookies","Black Pudding Croquettes",""]'),
(262, 262, 'VERMONT IPA V2.0', 'SMALL BATCH', '2016', 'JUICY, CITRUSY, TROPICAL.', '', 'A second trial of our previous  Small Batch Vermont IPA using a different yeast strain. A vermont style IPA, with low background bitterness, loaded with intense  juicy fruit characters.\r\n', '', 'DON’T add flour. This “tip” has been floating around for the style and it’s bad advice. Any and all murk should accompany something that enhances  the beer. This little juice-box is dry hopped at a rate of 10g per litre. Wonder what would happen if you doubled that...\r\n', '', 20, 25, 6.9, 1012, 1066, 15, 7.6, 4.2, 79, 35, 0, '{"65":75}', '19', '', '["Chicken Korma","Lobster Salad","Chicken and Apricot Tagine",""]');
